This app is great for making easy 3D pictures I can then view in 3D on my VR headset!

Whilst I've had some brilliant results from this app. There are a couple of niggles though: I would really like the app to open straightaway in camera mode. And, PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE, can we have location info embedded - it's so much easier to lookup batches via exif data than by renaming files!!

Did not work right after update. Needed to reinstall it.

Hi, I have a few things I would like to ask/suggest. When I use this app recently no matter how careful I am with not tilting it, one of the two photos gets always turned sideways which is annoying because I haven't found a way to turn only one photo and that makes all the photos I take unusable as stereos. Is there a way of turning only one photo, or is that a possible addition for future updates? If not I would seriously reconsider using this app because it gets frustrating.  And the second thing is that somehow the stereo pairs always get mixed up after a while, so for all my photos I can never see two matching photos side by side. It is always one of one stereo pair and one of the next. Another feature which makes this app unusable, and considering I'm paying for this app I'm not too happy. I hope there is a way of fixing/improving these things.  Another suggestion I have is a better way of navigating all photos because once you get to 100s it gets annoying trying to find one specific photo. What I also noticed is that if I take a photo and then go to an older photo, the new photo has disappeared. I have to close and reopen the app before I can see it again. Hope this helps!
I want my money back this app is Garbage if you want something better that can actually export your picture download Kula Scope this app is ass
Auto align is not as good as it should be. Stereo Photo Maker does a much better job of alignment. Otherwise it is the best 3D app available.
Much better than an app I had previously. Great fun and great 3D pics.
All I need on Neo3do.....Update 3D tablet has died ...maybe will now try Oculus.

Literally my favorite camera! Please consider to add; when saving a 3d picture give the option to save a custom set of 3d formats, like hit save 1x and save 2-3 preselected pics for example could save para, duboise, anaglyph, etc 3d versions all at once. Thank you for the awesome app! This app will never leave my phone! UPDATE 12/28/19: Still the best 3d camera on Android!

Disappointing because I'd rather edit photos on a touch screen, but will have to stick with the free "StereoPhoto Maker (English)" on my desktop machine.
I have been using this app more than five years. Still getting excellent results.

I've been wanting a stereo camera for years, but couldn't afford one. This is an incredible half way solution. Really solid 3d imaging and amazing auto solving. There are some basic improvments I'd like to see, which stopped me from giving 5 stars, mainly because you can't set a save destination. I'd prefer to br able to save straight to my sd card. The interface is pretty clunky too. But, it performs the main purpose incredibly well.

Great App! Wish it didn't show incompatability message when installing (please update as needed). Chose to continue and all seems to work as expected. PLEASE add BMP save option! Opens my BMP files, but saves as JPG. Need to retain original quality for quality printing. Thank You!

best app for 3d stereo, wiggle, red/blue, cross eyed, all in one! easy to edit and save 3d in many formats! With this app the only thing I can't do on my phone is save in MPO format. Highly recommend.

This is a fantastic app. The paid version includes the very useful auto-align feature which is worth paying for. If only the settings menu was easier to understand. The labels are the opposite way round. When there's a tick the statement is not true. When there's no tick it's still not true? Doesn't make sense. Can you leave it so the option doesn't change or so there is no tick, but the statement changes?
Thank you for the best 3D software.

This is by far the best mobile app I've tried so far for my Gadmei and LG Thrill. It's loading speed of high resolution images is fast, supports the Gadmei, which I was having trouble finding compatible apps and still am for it. Parallax adjustments are cool although I have not used them.  I noticed a minor glitch on my Gadmei, it does not zoom more then 100% where it does on my LG Thrill which I can live with.   I only have 1 issue with the entire app, other then that it is truly awesome. Some of my MPO's don't view right where it does in all other apps. Which I'm sure is a minor alignment glitch reading the mpo. Couple of things that I think might be cool.  -Auto Parallax alignment for viewing -and a 2D to 3D real-time converter for 2D images like cyberlink does Side note: I've been using your other apps on my PC for several yrs now.You have no idea how much you've made my life easy by developing your apps and giving them to the public.There is still not much in the way of 3D image editing out yet, or tools to batch edit or convert.I had 3D Steroid on my phone for a while, but did not realize it was by the same person until just now when I purchased the Pro Thank You
Looks like I am going to have fun!

A good app to have with my HTC EVO V to convert my 3D pictures to anaglyph so I can share easily with others without 3D devices. There are a few places that will send you free anaglyph (red/cyan) glasses for a self addressed stamped envelope. Do a Google search!
Use this app probably way too much
If you add "save as MPO format" then will give 5 stars. Otherwise this is good.
I spent a lot of time using PC-software to create 3D-images. It can be done, but... a lot of work. And now I install this app and bingo, two clicks and I have a perfect stereo image. What a surprise!

Easy, fast, automatic, and can be adjusted after the fact for a plethora of different 3D techniques. What more could I want?  The automatic alignment makes the paid version worthwhile. It greatly improves the ease of perceiving depth in pictures I take without requiring any manual adjustment work.

Started making 3D photos on my own just using a single camera and joining two photos on my PC. I started figuring someone must make a decent app to simplify this... And here it is! A little confusing at first, but once you play with it a little bit, it becomes easy to work with and has everything you need to make 3D photos flawless when using a single camera. Very well made app, only the second app I've actually shelled money out for!
This is perfect, however, it would be great if we could export a full resolution .gif when exporting a "wiggle" photograph.

I was unsure about this, so downloaded the free version first. Was quite impressed - enough to pay for the Pro version, which immediately made it much easier to produce very good 3D images. I had some old red and blue lens glasses to try it and yes, it does work! I'm going to get some of the 3DTV glasses and try some of the other formats too. Very good addition to my photo app collection, and respect to the developer for a quality bit of software.

Works pretty well and has several options for display. Only problem so far is saving and loading pics doesn't work reliably yet . saved and (re)loaded pics are messed up on my droid razor with ics.  Lots of fun though. I will be truly great w a couple of of patches!

My main interest in purchasing this program was to be able to make wigglegrams within my phone, using its built-in camera.  I played around with the program for quite a while, and was generally pleased with my progress, when I discovered that all of the files I had saved were not in fact animated GIFs but instead side-by-side JPGs.  Not having the ability to save in animated GIF makes this program useless to me.    Other than that, overall, the program seems to make sense, and potentially could have produced some pretty nice results.  I did have a couple of lockups (pretty severe ones, Galaxy Exhibit II 4G) but I was also bouncing back and forth between a couple of other programs.  Once I focused on this app, I didn't have another issue during the half hour or so I continued playing with it.    One thing that is really beginning to irritate me, not just with this app, but with a number that use the camera; give me access to my camera's settings.  There were a number of shots where the white balance was dead-wrong.  It would have been nice to override it.  Or to be able to manually determine the flash setting.  Or to be able to override the exposure setting.  Etc.
Very good application.
Best 3d photo app on the market, and could do with some updates though.... You know for bug fixing or to add new features, would be nice to be able to manage photos in gallery
Thank you for make it work with Gadmei  3d tablets ! The 3d auto adjustment is a good idea !

I had high hopes, and to be fair the first few stereograms really impressed me. But then it started to misbehave. Sometimes the app treats each of the two coresponding stereo shots as seperate files and doesn't always match them up for viewing, you get the right eye view from one stereogram and the left eye view from another. Not ideal. The programme must recognise the two views as a single file in order to work properly. Which it doesn't on my phone.

I love taking 3D pictures, and it's nice to have an app to assist with that process. About the only things I can see improving are the English translation, import from the free version, and a gallery feature. (Though the open file function does help there a bit.) The web galleries are a really nice touch too. It's fun to relive the days of Viewmaster. :)

I downloaded this based on everyone else's 5-star user reviews. Sadly, the camera "preview" screen is distorted and stretched horizontally, the help guide is accessed via a web connection only and is poorly translated from Japanese, and the app is buggy. After taking 2-3 pictures, it seems to revert to it's stock "intro" cartoon picture, and my photos don't appear at all. Not worth ¬£2.50 unless you fancy waiting until the glitches are ironed out...
This IS the best 3D app. I have purchased a few. Love it!

This is by far the best 3D app I've used and I've tried (and bought) many of them. It's so easy to use and it allows very high resolution pictures. It allows quick swap between Cross-Eyed view and Anaglyph so I can test while out and about, then save later for my glasses. The auto-align works like a charm and coupled with the onion-skin view makes the cleanest 3D I've seen on any of my devices.  The developer has thought of everything and then added even more. I am very pleased with this purchase and would have easily bought it for twice the price. If you are all interested in making 3D photos on your Android device, this is the way to go, hands down.
Works really well. Very happy. Thanks dev! :)

Please add timer followed by two consecutive shots at about 2 seconds in between to allow self portrait.  This way only the background will be 2d but the actual person who would move sideways will emboss himself as the 3d object.

Absolutely love it. Enough to actually pay for it. One minor thing though, on my S2 the zoom doesn't seem to work on playback? Not a big deal. Looking forward to more developments on this app. Thanks.

JUST, JUST AWESOME!!!!!!!!!!!!!!  This app is absolutely great, worth much more than 250 yen.
